My son asked me the other day who my best friend was. 

I told him that I don’t have one. 

I explained to him that I have had a very unique privilege of assembling a crew of not just one but several friends that are all close to me - and  all I consider my very best friends. 

I also told him that, because of this phenomenon,  he has a world wide network of very unique and talented uncles that I know would be there for him in a second - just as I would be for them. 

This weekend we got the news that we lost one of my son’s uncles - and a long time family friend Donnie Wedding. 

Donnie came into our life as many have - connected to our brand. 

As a firefighter in Fredericksburg
and very talented artist (Box Alarm Graphics!) Donnie had drawn up a concept he wanted made into a custom necklace and I proudly made for him his #78 padlock necklace. 

Unknowingly, at the time, Donnie had become my first custom client.  Through the process of making this for him - we became friends. 

This was 2005. 

(ish)

Over the years to follow Donnie has just been part of the picture and as our brand and business evolved he was always there to support. 
More importantly he was a part of it all. He was with us. 

He was then and always will be a component of our @room101brand family. A Day 1. 

My heart aches for the loss of my friend and one of my son’s finest uncles. 

I love you dude. I hope you rest easy and I truly hope you found the peace you were looking for.

Quick dip to Bend to see some old friends…

Now on to the next episode. 

WWW.SHADOWARMY.CO

Look at these two “sellouts” right here…

Huge congratulations to my brothers Alan, Ralph and the extended @alecbradleycigars family. 

I met Alan in 2009 and over the years he has been a friend and brother as well as a mentor. Most importantly - one of my son’s uncles. 
Family. 

I am so happy for you guys. You earned it. 

Shoutout to every warrior out there in the midst of their 20+ year grind. 

If you don’t stop - every sleepless night, every stomach ache, every door slammed in your face, betrayal, and gray hair that has built you will get you where you want to land. 

It is not a question of if - only of when and do you have the stones to see it through. 

This is a friendly reminder that The American Dream is still alive and well. 

Now go out there today and get after it.

It was the sweaty mid summer of ‘09

The “boutique” segment of our industry was just beginning to blossom. 

‘twas the salad days of craft cigars…

The cast of characters was short yet sturdy. 

The age of saturation was ahead.

A young aspiring brand architect who held an affinity for the combustion of dead plant rod happened upon the scene. 

He joined this small cast of characters and together they collectively terraformed the landscape of what was to become an undeniable and evergreen component of an industry - globally. 

So dramatic, no? 

But true. 

Shits a little different these days. Things continue to evolve (or devolve) - hair gets grey and the stripes have long since stacked up. 

 But I remember being in that moment - and I’m grateful the universe planted me in that space at that time and let me do my thing. 

Shit was magic.

We were all so busy making it happen I’m not sure any of us knew, that at that moment, we had lightening in the palm of our hands. 

But thats what we all do every day - make shit happen. 

Thanks for tuning in. Thank you for supporting all these years and we’re grateful to have you along for the ride. The next few chapters are gonna be bangers…

Shoutout to my man Thor and his family at @cigarpress for always showing us love and for the cover shot you currently feast your eyes on.
